description:
&lt;p&gt;A permanent opportunity has arisen within Solihull Home Treatment Team. This role is for a Band 6 Community Psychiatric Nurse.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will entail co-ordinating and providing specialist acute crisis psychiatric intervention and expertise to service users in crisis 24 hours per day, 7 days per week, 52 weeks per year within their own homes/residence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition, the team provides a gate-keeping service to inpatient wards; facilitating early discharge and providing an effective and viable alternative to hospital admission for clients in crisis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please consider joining Solihull Home Treatment Team; all staff are extremely friendly and professional. There is no doubt you will enjoy the experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDalbir MasanaJob titleSolihull Home Treatment Team ManagerTelephone number0121 301 4820&lt;/p&gt;
